<TEXT>
MR DAVID CLARK, Labour agriculture spokesman, yesterday dismissed the
'euphoria' shown by Mr John Gummer, agriculture minister, over the CAP deal.
'All the evidence we get is that the consumer will not benefit,' Mr Clark
said in the Commons.
He also said that the deal would not benefit small farmers. There were
