<HEADLINE>
FT  23 MAY 92 / Travel: Royal Viking Queen
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Because of a slip, last week's article on the Royal Viking Queen cruise-ship
stated that 'the average daily price paid by US clients for a two-week
cruise on the Queen is Dollars 9,500 per person.' As the article later made
clear, the Dollars 9,500 relates to 14 days' cruising - an average daily
price (per person) of Dollars 679.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page X
</PAGE>
</DOC>
