FT  23 MAY 92 / Leading Article: Lloyds referred
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR MICHAEL Heseltine has taken the right decision in referring the Lloyds
Bank bid for Midland to the Monopolies Commission. Unlike the bid from
Hongkong Bank, the Lloyds offer raises competition issues which need to be
scrutinised. And since the Hongkong bid has already been cleared in
Brussels, there are no awk-ward conflicts between rival competition
authorities. The odds are tilting in Hongkong's favour, but not
overwhelmingly so. Lloyds should keep its hat in the ring.
