<TEXT>
ALCOA, the world's largest producer of aluminium, and Al Zayani Investments
WWL of Bahrain are to form a joint venture to manufacture plastic bottle
caps for the growing Middle Eastern beverage market, writes Barbara Durr.
Under the deal, to be completed next month, the venture, called Gulf
Closures, will immediately begin construction of a new plant in Bahrain. The
plant is scheduled for start-up in the first quarter of 1993 and will
produce over 200m compression-moulded plastic closures by the end of next
year.
Al Zayani Investments has interests in banking, services tendering, hotels,
property and light manufacturing.
