<HEADLINE>
FT  22 MAY 92 / UK Company News: Drayton Cons writes Pounds 47m off assets
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN, Investments Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DRAYTON Consolidated Trust, the investment trust company specialising in
unquoted assets, said yesterday that it had written off more than half the
value of its unlisted assets to Pounds 40.1m at the end of March from Pounds
87m just six months earlier.
The company, which is managed by Invesco MIM, also said that its advisers,
County NatWest Wood Mackenzie and Cazenove, had recommended proposals for
the remaining assets which would allow shareholders to receive cash as
assets were sold.
The advisers were appointed in February following the announcement that
receivers had been appointed to Alma Holdings, the unquoted confectionery
company in which Drayton was the main shareholder.
In its statement yesterday, Drayton said the sharp drop in valuation of the
unquoted portfolio over the past six months largely reflected the write-off
in Alma Holdings as well as write-offs against the value of property
occupied by City Merchants Bank and by further provisions against other
unspecified investments.
Drayton said its advisers were suggesting the formation of a new quoted
investment company which would hold the unquoted investments until they
could be sold in an orderly manner. The new company would also own several
quoted, but illiquid, investments. Meanwhile, as the remaining assets are
sold, shareholders will receive cash.
At end-March the trust's current assets were valued at Pounds 86.3m, down
from Pounds 162m at the end of September 1991. Gross income for the half
year to March 31 fell to Pounds 3.98m (Pounds 5.05m). The interim dividend
is maintained at 4.25p.
</TEXT>
