<TEXT>
ITALY'S privatisation programme moved a small step forward yesterday with
the transfer of formal control of Seleco, one of the country's best-known
consumer electronics companies, to a group of private investors headed by Mr
Gian Mario Rossignolo and Mr Hans Werthen.
Mr Rossignolo is chairman of Zanussi, the Italian white goods group owned by
